
@startuml

class Student {
  -studentId: String
  -name: String
  -email: String
  -registeredCourses: List<Course>
}

class TeachingAssistant {
  -taId: String
  -name: String
  -email: String
  -teachingCourses: List<Course>
}

class Course {
  -courseCode: String
  -courseName: String
  -description: String
}

class Appointment {
  -appointmentId: String
  -date: Date
  -time: Time
  -duration: Integer
  -student: Student
  -teachingAssistant: TeachingAssistant
  -course: Course
}

Student "1" -- "0..*" Appointment : requests
TeachingAssistant "1" -- "0..*" Appointment : provides
Course "1" -- "0..*" Appointment : related to

Student "1" -- "0..*" Course : registered for
TeachingAssistant "1" -- "0..*" Course : teaches

note right of Appointment
  An appointment is always for one specific course and with one TA who teaches that course.
end note
@enduml

### Explanation:
- **Student**: Can request appointments only for courses they are registered in.
- **TeachingAssistant**: Can provide help only for the courses they are teaching.
- **Course**: Has many appointments, each linked to one student and one TA.
- **Appointment**: Is associated with exactly one student, one TA, and one course.

